metadata.name: MIAB #2 (RESEARCH RIG)
metadata.description: A research rig in the ocean where B.O.B or multiple vessels can dock to exchange and share information with other scientists. The station accesses energy through solar panels and surrounding wind turbines, as well as the turbines from the docking B.O.Bâ€™s.

attributes.value: Self sufficient living onboard renewable food supplies and carbon positive design
Built from the existing structure of a decommissioned oil rig. Recycling old technology into a forward-thinking research facility
